Carcinoid tumor in the retroperitoneal space. Authors present a rare case of the pancreatic carcinoid. Diagnosis was based on clinical examination, ultrasonography, CT, and histopathological evaluation. The patient was operated on twice: (Whipple's procedure with the right hemicolectomy and then Roux-Y anastomosis). During follow-up the liver metastases appeared. The patient was treated with chemotherapy. She died 19 month after operation because of neoplastic dissemination.